• identify meaningful urban design issues through on-site observation and reviewing relevant literature;
• apply visual communication techniques—mapping—to document and effectively reveal the understanding of the selected site and the identified issue;
• develop creative design approaches to tackle the identified urban issue;
• nurture critical thinking in issues associated with the urban built environment and their implications for local communities and society.

